### Forecasting Implementation Path ‚Äì SQL-Native Option (Updated Blurb)

For the E-22 forecasting capability, a viable path forward is to implement the cycle-time and forecasting calculations **natively in Tableau using SQL**. Based on recent discussions, the core cycle-time and moving-range logic already exists in SQL in other environments (e.g., NPD), and this logic can be reused or aligned for E-22 rather than rebuilt.

In this approach, Tableau parameters would allow users to adjust forecasting assumptions (such as projected production or time horizon), and Tableau would re-execute the SQL directly, enabling on-the-fly updates to the visualizations. This keeps the solution fully within Tableau, avoids dependency on DBIS enabling TabPy, and reduces technical and schedule risk while still meeting the interactive forecasting requirement.

TabPy and Power Apps remain viable alternative paths if needed, but the SQL-native approach provides a lower-risk, more immediately actionable option.

